headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 33 points in three quarters and the Memphis Grizzlies led by as many as 31 points in a 135-115 win over the Orlando Magic on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ja Morant scores 33, leads Grizzlies' 135-115 rout of Magic

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 27 points, Bam Adebayo added 20 points and 12 rebounds and the Miami Heat used a dominant third quarter to hand the struggling Charlotte Hornets their fourth straight loss, 104-86 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler, Adebayo lead Heat past frustrated Hornets 104-86

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had 20 points and 16 rebounds in an efficient 24 minutes and the NBA-leading Phoenix Suns rebounded from a streak-ending loss to beat the short-handed Washington Wizards 95-80 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton has 20 points and 16 rebounds, Suns rout Wizards

events.name: New York Knicks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James returned from a five-game absence due to injury and had a triple-double of 29 points, 13 rebounds, 10 assists, and the Los Angeles Lakers rallied from a 21-point, second-quarter deficit, beating the New York Knicks 122-115 in overtime...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron returns with triple-double, Lakers beat Knicks in OT

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Bobby Portis Jr. had a season-high 30 points, including six 3-pointers, and the Milwaukee Bucks handed the Portland Trail Blazers their fifth straight loss, 137-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portis scores 30, Bucks rout Trail Blazers 137-108

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes had 24 points and nine rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings held on to beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 113-103 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes scores 24, Kings hold on to beat Thunder 113-103
